      "parts": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The simplest solution: run everything inside WSL2\n\nInstead of trying to reach WSL2 Flask from Windows via localhost, do all commands in WSL2:\n\nRun Flask backend in WSL2:\n\ncd ~/visual-task/visual-interaction/backend\npython3 app.py\n\nFlask will run on 0.0.0.0:5000 and 172.20.199.176:5000.\n\nRun Flutter frontend in WSL2:\n\ncd ~/visual-task/visual-interaction/frontend\nflutter run -d web-server --web-port=0 --web-hostname=0.0.0.0\n\nFlutter will print a URL like:\n\nhttp://127.0.0.1:46409/\n\nAccess Flutter web in Windows:\n\nOpen browser and replace 127.0.0.1 with WSL2 IP:\n\nhttp://172.20.199.176:46409/\n\nNow the Flutter frontend is served by WSL2 and can call the Flask backend using the same IP:\n\nconst String API_BASE_URL = 'http://172.20.199.176:5000';   make this will work in ubuntu and make changes",
          "id": "prt_cfe375c6a001hK8vLcyqWa57Lw",
          "sessionID": "ses_301c8a3b1ffe4tadFrf32EicO2",
          "messageID": "msg_cfe375c67001b2IImSHyJ8cvaA"
        }
      ]
